```c++
#include <iostream>

int guess(int num) {
    if (num > n) return -1;
    else if (num < n) return 1;
    else return 0;
}

class Solution {
public:
    int guessNumber(int n) {
        while (true) {
            int guess = guess(n);
            if (guess == 0) return n;
            n = guess;
        }
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution uses a while loop to repeatedly call the `guess` function until the correct number is guessed. The `guess` function returns -1 if the guess is higher, 1 if the guess is lower, and 0 if the guess is correct. The loop continues until the correct number is guessed, which results in a high efficiency. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because the loop will terminate after a logarithmic number of guesses. The space complexity is O(1) because the solution uses a constant amount of space. The energy implications are low because the solution only involves simple arithmetic operations and does not consume significant energy.

